Checking Locations Report

Kendra Wyant

2020-09-18

  • Notes
  • Setup
  • Import Data and glimpse
  • Descriptives

Notes

This script checks data from RISK participants locations reports by computing descriptives and checking for missingness and potential errors.

Thoughts for discussion:
1. Time of visit refers to study visit when location was identified. How can we link to gps data with time of location visit?
2. Location_type other was 2nd most common choice. Locate paper files to analyze what these locations are.
3. Not much variability in yes and no questions. Ex: Less than 4% answered yes to vacationing at location question.

Paths

getwd()
## [1] "/Volumes/private/StudyData/RISK"

Check for missing values

if(any(is.na(locations))){
  missing <- locations %>%
    summarise(across(everything(), ~sum(is.na(.)))) %>%
    gather(key = "var", value = "num_NA" ) %>%
    filter(num_NA > 0)
  missing %>%
    kable(caption = "Variables with missing values", table.attr = "style='width:40%;'") %>%
    kable_styling(position = "left", bootstrap_options = "condensed")
}else {
  paste("No missing values")
}

A google map search of 1222 East Washington Avenue, WI confirms city should be Madison. Will add city.

Add city to city variable and full_address variable

locations_137 <- locations %>% 
  filter(subid == 137 & street_address == "1222 East Washington Avenue") %>% 
  mutate(city = "Madison",
         full_address = str_glue("{street_address}, {city}, {state}"))
locations <- locations %>%
  filter(!(subid == 137 & street_address == "1222 East Washington Avenue"))
locations <- locations %>% 
  rbind(locations_137)

Descriptives

Locations outside Madison (city)

locations %>% 
  select(city) %>%
  mutate(city = case_when(
    city == "Madison" ~ "Madison",
    TRUE ~ "Outside Madison")) %>% 
  tabyl(city, show_na = TRUE) %>% 
  adorn_totals("row") %>%
  kable(table.attr = "style='width:50%;'") %>%
  kable_styling(position = "left")
city n percent
Madison 3223 0.6161346
Outside Madison 2008 0.3838654
Total 5231 1.0000000

Average number of places participants reported each visit

mean_avg_location_per_day <- locations %>%                                                          
  group_by(subid, date(time_central)) %>% 
  summarise(n_obs = n()) %>% 
  group_by(subid) %>% 
  summarise(avg_locations_per_day = mean(n_obs)) %>% 
  .$avg_locations_per_day %>% 
  mean()

max_location_per_day <- locations %>% 
  group_by(subid, date(time_central)) %>% 
  summarise(n_obs = n()) %>% 
  group_by(subid) %>% 
  summarise(max = max(n_obs)) %>% 
  .$max %>% max()

locations %>% 
  group_by(subid, date(time_central)) %>% 
  summarise(n_obs = n()) %>% 
  group_by(subid) %>%
  summarise(avg_locations_per_day = mean(n_obs)) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = avg_locations_per_day)) +
  geom_histogram(bins = 12) +
  xlab("avg locations participants reported per visit") +
  ggtitle("Histogram of average locations reported per day (visit)") +
  theme_classic()

On average, participants reported an average of 9.96 places visisted at their intake/followup visits (max = 58).

COMMENT KW 2020-08-11: The goal would be to use the above script to report the places participants visited each day if we can combine these locations with GPS data. Currently it probably does not tell us much because we would expect participants reported more locations at intake and fewer at followups.

Location as a function of risk level

locations %>%
  mutate(type = tolower(type),
         type = fct_infreq(factor(type))) %>%
  mutate(risk = tolower(risk),
         risk = fct_relevel(factor(risk, c("high", "medium", "low", "no", "NA")))) %>% 
  ggplot(aes (x = type, fill = risk)) +
  geom_bar() +
  xlab("location type") +
  ggtitle("Frequency plot of types of locations visited by risk level") +
  theme_classic() +  
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  scale_fill_brewer(palette = "BuPu", direction = -1, na.value = "light grey")
